    <fr:title text="A criteria of being Heyting">A criteria of being Heyting</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Unsolved</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a distributive lattice where for each point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex>, the stalk <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A/x]]></fr:tex> is a Heyting algebra. Is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> necessarily Heyting?
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
