            <fr:title text="Can being Heyting checked on stalks?">Can being Heyting checked on stalks?</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  We know from <fr:link href="/schm-LL5B/" title="Being Heyting/Boolean is affine local" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LL5B/" display-uri="schm-LL5B" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LL5B/" display-uri="schm-LL5B" /></fr:link> that being Heyting is affine local. Furthermore, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-FZCT/" title="Heyting and Boolean schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FZCT/" display-uri="schm-FZCT" type="local">Heyting scheme</fr:link>, then evidently for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>, the stalk <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X,x}]]></fr:tex> is a local Heyting algebra. However, is the converse true, i.e. is being Heyting a <fr:link href="/schm-HE7H/" title="Stalk local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-HE7H/" display-uri="schm-HE7H" type="local">stalk local</fr:link> property?
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  The related question for Boolean algebras is positive, since being Boolean is <html:em>geometric</html:em>, i.e. for a sheaf of distributive lattice <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, it is Boolean iff it satisfies the following geometric sequent,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \top  \vdash _{x\in \mathcal {O}_{X}} \exists  y \in  \mathcal {O}_{X}.\  (x \wedge  y = 0) \wedge  (x \vee  y = 1) ]]></fr:tex>
  However, it seems to be quite hard to come up with a geometric description of being Heyting. This ultimately reduces to an <fr:link href="/idem-comm-I4FM/" title="A criteria of being Heyting" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-I4FM/" display-uri="idem-comm-I4FM" type="local">algebraic problem</fr:link>.
</html:p>
